      • dereferenceHeaderSpace

        public static HeaderSpace dereferenceHeaderSpace(HeaderSpace headerSpace,
                                                 java.util.Map<java.lang.String,IpSpace> namedIpSpaces)
                                          throws CircularReferenceException,
                                                 UndefinedReferenceException
        Constructs a sanitized HeaderSpace where all IpSpaceReferences are replaced with their dereferenced IpSpaces.
        Parameters:
        headerSpace - The header space whose IpSpaces to dereference
        namedIpSpaces - Named IP spaces in the context of the given header space.
        Returns:
        A version of the given header space with all IpSpace fields dereferenced.
        Throws:
        {@link - CircularReferenceException} if any IpSpace in the header space points to a cyclical reference.
        {@link - UndefinedReferenceException} if any IpSpace in the header space points to an undefined reference.
        CircularReferenceException
        UndefinedReferenceException
